<headline>Severe Thunderstorm Warning issued June 23 at 4:19PM MDT until June 23 at 4:45PM MDT by NWS Glasgow</headline>
<description>...A SEVERE THUNDERSTORM WARNING REMAINS IN EFFECT UNTIL 445 PM MDT
FOR SOUTHWESTERN DANIELS...NORTHWESTERN ROOSEVELT AND EASTERN VALLEY
COUNTIES...
At 419 PM MDT, a severe thunderstorm was located 9 miles northwest of
Lustre, or 30 miles southeast of Opheim, moving east at 40 mph.
HAZARD...60 mph wind gusts and small hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Expect damage to roofs, siding, and trees.
Locations impacted include...
Lustre and Volt.
HAIL THREAT...RADAR INDICATED
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.75 IN
WIND THREAT...RADAR INDICATED
MAX WIND GUST...60 MPH</description>
<instruction>For your protection move to an interior room on the lowest floor of a
building.</instruction>
